    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel your <strong>potatoes</strong> and chop them into large, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>potatoes</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender, then drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-and-red-wine-stew-with-horseradish-mash/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and cut your <strong>shallot[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Top, tail, peel and slice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> into discs on the diagonal</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-and-red-wine-stew-with-horseradish-mash/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive</strong> <strong>oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>shallot</strong> <strong>wedges</strong> and <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>carrot</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-and-red-wine-stew-with-horseradish-mash/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the veg is softening, dissolve your <strong>beef</strong> <strong>stock</strong> <strong>mix</strong>, <strong>tomato</strong> <strong>paste</strong> and <strong>red</strong> <strong>wine</strong> <strong>paste</strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[320ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[420ml]</span> <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>red wine stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-and-red-wine-stew-with-horseradish-mash/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the carrot and onion has slightly softened, add your <strong>mince</strong> to the pan with your <strong>bay leaf[ves]</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Once browned, reduce the heat to medium-high, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> and 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-and-red-wine-stew-with-horseradish-mash/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>red wine stock</strong> with a grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-high and cook for 4-5 min or until the sauce has thickened and the mince is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your<strong> red wine stew</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-and-red-wine-stew-with-horseradish-mash/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the<strong> cooked potatoes</strong> to a low heat with a small knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>horseradish</strong> <strong>sauce</strong> (not a big horseradish fan? Try using less!)<strong> </strong>and mash until smooth \u2013 this is your <strong>horseradish mash</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-and-red-wine-stew-with-horseradish-mash/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>red wine stew</strong> over the <strong>horseradish</strong> <strong>mash</strong>, discard the <strong>bay leaf[ves]</strong></p><p>Season with a grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and garnish with the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>parsley</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
